Abandoned

in favor of shell tests
Hmm, does it help that we can already type `~.` (SSH-style escape) to disconnect? Is there benefit to adding another way that only works if you're running the process locally?
Probably should have marked this one as unresolved.

It's good that there is that possibility but for writing tests i prefer something more direct.

The SIGINT approach does not need any pipe to the client, it only needs the PID. So it is more flexible and does not need much setup. It will help to keep the tests short.

Bit of a nit, but `sig_atomic_t` is defined as an integer type, and integer types with static storage duration are defined to be initialised to zero by default, so the assignment of `false` isn't strictly necessary. Also, given it's not explicitly a `bool` (any more than any integer in C can look like a bool) I'd mildly prefer we avoid using `true`/`false` as well.
Done
